The paper deals with the problem of learning restricted Boltzmann machines in the presence of relational data. This problem is closely related to machine learning, artificial intelligence, and databases. The paper also discusses the interpretability and explainability of the learned models, which is a topic of interest in natural language processing and computational linguistics. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DB (Databases). The paper also involves some aspects of natural language processing and computational linguistics, which are covered by cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
